headline: Lockheed Martin's Dip On Great Results Doesn't Mean To Buy
summary: Lockheed Martin saw growth across key segments, increased its dividend by 5%, and expanded its share buyback program to $9.1 billion. Read why LMT is a Hold.

headline: TransDigm (TDG): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q2 Earnings?
summary: TransDigm has been treading water for the past six months, holding steady at $1,302. The stock also fell short of the S&P 500’s 30.6% gain during that period.
